      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "faith",
      "excerpt": "Source: titus-jr-laxa — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/blinded-by-sin\nPublished: 2024-12-16 --- Three ways Christians can be blinded by their own sin: 1. Blinded by sin's danger — We easily see the danger of other people's...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"blinded-by-sin\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Blinded by Sin</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/blinded-by-sin\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2024-12-16</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"summary\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Summary</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Three ways Christians can be blinded by their own sin:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Blinded by sin&#39;s danger</strong> — We easily see the danger of other people&#39;s sins, but when it comes to our own, all we see are the benefits, not the harm. We convince ourselves our case is different.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Blinded by sin&#39;s deepness</strong> — Sin doesn&#39;t start with a bang. It starts with a spark, then turns to a fire you cannot quench. A pastor who commits adultery didn&#39;t wake up one day and decide to sin — it began with gradual coldness, then emotional bonding, then sudden fall.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Blinded by sin&#39;s denial</strong> — We justify our sin as a natural response to being sinned against. We think God gives a pass for someone to sin when they have become victims.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h1 id=\"key-quote\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Quote</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;When we are blinded by our sin, we are like Cain, whom God had to warn about how his jealousy with Abel is letting sin crouch at the door.&quot;</blockquote>\n<h1 id=\"what-to-do-if-blind\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">What to do if blind</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Ask God to open your eyes to your sin, not morbidly, but humbly (Psalm 139:23-24)</li>\n<li>Confess sins honestly, without qualification or excuse (1 John 1:9)</li>\n<li>Set your hope on Christ and His powerful grace to change you (1 Peter 1:13-16)</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"connections\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Connections</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sin</a> — The doctrine of hamartiology; how sin blinds us to itself</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=temptation</a> — The anatomy of falling; sin starts small then grows</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sanctification</a> — The ongoing work of God transforming the believer</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=confession</a> — Calling sin by name without excuse</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"sources-updated\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Sources Updated</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=temptation</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
