      "domain": "general",
      "excerpt": "Source: titus-jr-laxa — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/restoring-broken-people\nPublished: 2024-12-02 --- Brokenness means being unable to do what God calls you to do because of what's going on inside you. Ruth 3 shows...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"restoring-broken-people\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Restoring Broken People</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/restoring-broken-people\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2024-12-02</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"summary\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Summary</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Brokenness means being unable to do what God calls you to do because of what&#39;s going on inside you. Ruth 3 shows signs, struggles, and salvation from brokenness through Naomi&#39;s story.</p>\n<h1 id=\"signs-of-brokenness\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Signs of Brokenness</h1>\n<ol>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Possessed by a spirit of fear</strong> — Naomi didn&#39;t want Ruth to follow her, fearing they would suffer as she was suffering (Ruth 1:10-11)</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Overwhelmed by a spirit of bitterness</strong> — Naomi asked to be called &quot;Mara&quot; (bitter) because the Almighty had dealt bitterly with her (Ruth 1:20)</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Filled with a spirit of unbelief</strong> — Naomi saw God as the one who takes away blessings and brings calamity (Ruth 1:21)</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Brokenness is being overcome with fear, bitterness, and unbelief to the point you can no longer function.</p>\n<h1 id=\"struggles-with-brokenness\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Struggles with Brokenness</h1>\n<ol>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">It happens to anyone</strong> — Tragedies, troubles, and transgression can happen to the best of us. Naomi was a normal Israelite who experienced unexpected brokenness.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Nothing seems to fix it</strong> — Naomi tried changing location and people, but her bitterness came with her.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h1 id=\"salvation-from-brokenness\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Salvation from Brokenness</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">To be restored means to repair what is broken and make it as if it is not broken.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Signs of restoration:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Finding courage again — Naomi starts thinking like a mother, wanting good for Ruth (Ruth 3:1)</li>\n<li>Starting to obey again — Naomi instructs Ruth according to God&#39;s law (Deuteronomy 25)</li>\n<li>Starting to believe again — Naomi says &quot;Wait, my daughter&quot; (Ruth 3:18), showing faith that Boaz will act</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"how-god-restores\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">How God Restores</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Through His kindness — Reminded that God was still in control (Ruth 2:20)</li>\n<li>Through His presence — God&#39;s providence signals His presence in ordinary lives</li>\n<li>Through His promises — &quot;Humble yourselves before the Lord, and he will exalt you&quot; (James 4:10)</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"connections\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Connections</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sanctification</a> — God&#39;s ongoing restoration work</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=lament</a> — Honest grief brought to God</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=trials</a> — Suffering that exposes brokenness</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"sources-updated\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Sources Updated</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sanctification</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=trials</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
