      "excerpt": "Source: titus-jr-laxa — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/vanilla-ice-cream-over-cow-dung\nPublished: 2024-11-04 --- Our knee-jerk reaction to sin is to hide — like covering cow dung with vanilla ice cream. It looks nice on the...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"vanilla-ice-cream-over-cow-dung\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Vanilla Ice Cream Over Cow Dung</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> — tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/vanilla-ice-cream-over-cow-dung\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2024-11-04</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"summary\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Summary</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Our knee-jerk reaction to sin is to hide — like covering cow dung with vanilla ice cream. It looks nice on the outside but still smells. Genesis 3 shows four ways we hide.</p>\n<h1 id=\"four-ways-we-hide\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Four Ways We Hide</h1>\n<ol>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">We hide ourselves from one another</strong> (Genesis 3:7) — Adam and Eve sewed fig leaves. When we sin, we feel the need to hide — covering lies with more lies, hiding lust with violent head-turns, covering chat messages with passwords.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">We help each other hide</strong> (Genesis 3:7) — They covered themselves together. We hide one another&#39;s sins by not talking about them, by minimizing ugliness (&quot;we all struggle&quot;), by talking about others&#39; sins instead.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">We hide from God</strong> (Genesis 3:8) — When they heard God walking, they hid. We hide by not being in church, or by being distanced in church — folding arms, analyzing the preacher&#39;s flaws instead of facing our hearts.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">We hide with excuses</strong> (Genesis 3:9-10) — Adam said he was afraid because he was naked, not because he sinned. We point to consequences rather than the sin itself.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h1 id=\"what-39-s-wrong-with-hiding\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">What&#39;s Wrong with Hiding?</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;If we say we have fellowship with him while we walk in darkness, we lie and do not practice the truth.&quot; — 1 John 1:6</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Sin hidden is not sin removed. Sin unremoved is destructive. James 1:15: &quot;Sin when it is fully grown brings forth death.&quot;</p>\n<h1 id=\"god-39-s-solution\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">God&#39;s Solution</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;And the Lord God made for Adam and for his wife garments of skins and clothed them.&quot; — Genesis 3:21</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">God made the covering. A living being was sacrificed — blood was involved. This points to the Lamb of God who takes away the sins of the world. Christ cleanses sin that clings so closely.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Trust Him by confessing instead of hiding.</strong></p>\n<h1 id=\"connections\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Connections</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sin</a> — The problem we try to hide</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=confession</a> — Calling sin by name</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a> — Christ&#39;s blood as the true covering</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"sources-updated\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Sources Updated</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sin</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
