      "slug": "source-template",
      "title": "Source Template",
      "type": "template",
      "tags": [
        "research",
        "methodology"
      ],
      "created": "Wed Apr 15 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Wed Apr 15 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 0,
      "domain": "general",
      "excerpt": "Format for capturing sources during research. --- Type: [Primary / Expert Secondary / Quality Journalism / General Reporting / Opinion / Unreliable] Tier: [1-6, matching type] Citation: [Full citation in standard...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"source-template\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Source Template</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Format for capturing sources during research.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"template\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Template</h1>\n<pre class=\"bg-surface-container-low p-6 my-8 overflow-x-auto text-sm font-mono text-on-surface-variant\"><code>### [Source Title]\n\n**Type**: [Primary / Expert Secondary / Quality Journalism / General Reporting / Opinion / Unreliable]\n\n**Tier**: [1-6, matching type]\n\n**Citation**: [Full citation in standard format]\n\n**URL**: [Link if available]\n\n**Date**: [Publication date]\n\n**Author**: [Author name and credentials]\n\n**Publisher**: [Publication or platform]\n\n**Author Perspective**: [What perspective does the author bring? Bias?]\n\n**Key Claims**:\n1. [Claim 1]\n2. [Claim 2]\n3. [Claim 3]\n\n**Evidence**: [What evidence does the author provide?]\n\n**How Used**: [Which lens used this source, for what purpose]\n\n**Confidence**: [How confident are we in this source?]\n\n**Cross-References**: [Other sources that confirm or contradict]</code></pre>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"tier-definitions\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Tier Definitions</h1>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Tier</th>\n<th>Type</th>\n<th>Use</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Primary</td>\n<td>Foundation for arguments</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Expert Secondary</td>\n<td>Interpretation and synthesis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Quality Journalism</td>\n<td>Leads for deeper sources</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>General Reporting</td>\n<td>Awareness, not evidence</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Opinion</td>\n<td>Identify questions, not answers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Unreliable</td>\n<td>Discard or use only when no alternatives</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"special-cases\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Special Cases</h1>\n<h1 id=\"scripture\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Scripture</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">For theological lens:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Type: Primary</li>\n<li>Tier: 1</li>\n<li>Authority: Highest</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"ai-generated-content\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">AI-Generated Content</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Type: Depends on verification</li>\n<li>Only use if human-verified and sources cited</li>\n<li>Use for leads, not as final source</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"self-interested-sources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Self-Interested Sources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Note financial or ideological interest</li>\n<li>Use alongside disinterested sources</li>\n<li>Treat with extra skepticism</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"example\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Example</h1>\n<h1 id=\"the-economic-impact-of-ai-on-white-collar-work\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Economic Impact of AI on White-Collar Work</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Type</strong>: Expert Secondary\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Tier</strong>: 2\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Citation</strong>: McKinsey Global Institute. (2024). &quot;The Economic Impact of AI on White-Collar Work.&quot;\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">URL</strong>: <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">https://example.com/report</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Date</strong>: 2024-03-15\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author</strong>: McKinsey Global Institute\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Publisher</strong>: McKinsey &amp; Company\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author Perspective</strong>: Business consulting firm; pro-technology perspective; clients include tech companies\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Key Claims</strong>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>30% of white-collar tasks could be automated by 2030</li>\n<li>Jobs will be transformed more than eliminated</li>\n<li>Reskilling costs are lower than replacement costs\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Evidence</strong>: Survey of 500 companies; economic modeling; case studies\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">How Used</strong>: Economic lens (incentive structures, market dynamics)\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Confidence</strong>: Medium — well-researched but sponsored research\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Cross-References</strong>: Confirmed by World Economic Forum report; contradicts some labor economist predictions</li>\n</ol>\n",
