      "domain": "ministry",
      "excerpt": "Author: michael-foster\nSource: https://www.thisisfoster.com/p/a-common-danger-in-house-churches\nPublished: 2026-01-10 Modern house church movements harbor two interlocking spiritual dangers: they become refuges for...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"a-common-danger-in-house-churches\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">A Common Danger in House Churches</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=michael-foster</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">https://www.thisisfoster.com/p/a-common-danger-in-house-churches</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2026-01-10</p>\n<h1 id=\"summary\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Summary</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Modern house church movements harbor two interlocking spiritual dangers: they become refuges for unaccountable, manipulative men, and they operate from a restorationist delusion that severs believers from historic Christianity. The danger is not the house itself—it&#39;s a church with no past, no courts, no officers, no accountability, and no protection.</p>\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Points</h1>\n<h1 id=\"not-about-the-building\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Not About the Building</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The New Testament church gathered wherever God made space: homes (Acts 2:46; 5:42; Rom. 16:5), temple courts (Acts 2:46; 3:1–11), synagogues (Acts 9:20; 13:14–16), borrowed halls (Acts 19:9–10), riversides (Acts 16:13). The church was never tied to one kind of space.</p>\n<h1 id=\"danger-1-refuge-for-unaccountable-men\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Danger 1: Refuge for Unaccountable Men</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">When there is no formal eldership, no recognized courts, no mechanism for discipline, authority doesn&#39;t disappear—it goes feral. Someone always leads. The only question is whether that authority is visible, tested, and constrained, or hidden, personalized, and untouchable.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">House-church movements attract men who resent oversight, bristle at peer leadership, and despise institutional restraint. They speak of &quot;organic church&quot; and &quot;relational authority&quot; but mean no one gets to tell them no. In that environment, families have no protection.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The New Testament assumes plural eldership (Acts 14:23; Phil. 1:1), tested character (1 Tim. 3; Titus 1), public ordination (Acts 6:5–6; 13:3), discipline (Matt. 18:15–17; 1 Cor. 5), and appeal beyond local leaders (Acts 11; 15).</p>\n<h1 id=\"danger-2-the-restorationist-delusion\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Danger 2: The Restorationist Delusion</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Many house-church systems assume the church &quot;quickly fell&quot; after the apostles, was corrupted by structure and continuity, and must now be rebuilt from scratch. The language is &quot;We&#39;re getting back to Acts.&quot;</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">This mindset teaches that for most of two thousand years, Christ failed to preserve His church. That the Spirit largely abandoned her. That creeds, councils, and institutional forms were mostly mistakes. The real church has finally been rediscovered in someone&#39;s living room.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">This produces theological instability. You lose the guardrails that preserved doctrine through centuries. You trade tested consensus for private interpretations of a few modern leaders.</p>\n<h1 id=\"how-they-combine\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">How They Combine</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Restorationism creates leaders who believe they are rebuilding Christianity from scratch. Unaccountable structures give those leaders room to act like apostles. Together they produce small, intense, personality-driven communities that feel pure until they fracture, burn out, or wound the people inside.</p>\n<h1 id=\"related-concepts\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related Concepts</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=church-accountability</a> — plural eldership, tested character, courts of appeal</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=biblical-manhood</a> — men who lead with accountability, not evasion</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=providence</a> — God&#39;s preservation of His church through history</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"applications\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Applications</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">For those considering house churches: ask about eldership, about courts of appeal, about accountability structures. The New Testament church was not anti-institutional—it appointed officers, guarded doctrine, disciplined members, and formally transmitted the faith.</p>\n<h1 id=\"quotes\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Quotes</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;House-church worlds often promise freedom from hierarchy, but what they usually deliver is the most dangerous hierarchy of all: one man, self-appointed, immune to correction.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;To reject the historic church is not to recover the early church. It is to cut yourself off from her.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;The danger is not the house. The danger is a church with no past, no courts, no officers, no accountability, and no protection.&quot;</blockquote>\n",
