      "created": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "general",
      "excerpt": "Author: titus-jr-laxa\nPublished: 2025-02-05\nSource: tituslaxajr.substack.com A practical guide to biblical faithfulness in love and marriage, using Boaz (Ruth 4) as the model. Written for Christian men navigating a...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"a-field-guide-to-being-a-faithful-man\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">A Field Guide to Being A Faithful Man</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2025-02-05\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> tituslaxajr.substack.com</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">A practical guide to biblical faithfulness in love and marriage, using Boaz (Ruth 4) as the model. Written for Christian men navigating a culture that offers no good examples of how to love well.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Points</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">1. A faithful man respects God&#39;s law.</strong>\nBoaz sought permission from the prior redeemer before elders and witnesses — even though he had every desire to act immediately. Contrast with the judges (Samson, Jephthah, Barak) who followed passions over God&#39;s commands. A faithful man gives weight to God&#39;s law over his feelings.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">2. A faithful man is committed even when it&#39;s costly.</strong>\nThe other redeemer withdrew when he realized the cost. Boaz did not. Many godly men delay marriage for prudential reasons (saving money, awaiting parental approval, supporting siblings) — but in doing so, they signal to their future wife that she is less important than those goals.</p>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;Young men, feelings follow commitment, not the other way around.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">3. A faithful man honors his commitment.</strong>\nAfter committing, Boaz immediately took Ruth as his wife. Courtship is a commitment directed toward marriage. What sustains a relationship through incompatibility is not chemistry but humility — to recognize you are both sinners, to forgive, and to remain committed despite the world offering &quot;better options.&quot;</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">4. Jesus is the ultimate faithful man.</strong>\nBoaz is a type; Christ is the antitype — faithful unto death on a cross to redeem His people (Phil. 2:8).</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"concepts-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Concepts touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=biblical-manhood</a> — the core theme</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=courtship</a> — commitment in pursuing a spouse</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a> — Jesus as the faithful redeemer</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"related-resources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related resources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=where-have-the-men-gone</a> — the absence of confident godly men in courtship</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=beware-of-the-zone-of-vulnerability</a> — warning about emotional attachment to unbelievers</li>\n</ul>\n",
