      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "general",
      "excerpt": "Author: titus-jr-laxa\nPublished: 2024-12-17\nSource: tituslaxajr.substack.com Part of the \"Dear Darla\" epistolary series. A pastoral letter addressing a Christian woman who has fallen in love with an unbeliever and is...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"beware-of-the-zone-of-vulnerability\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Beware of the Zone of Vulnerability</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2024-12-17\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> tituslaxajr.substack.com</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Part of the &quot;Dear Darla&quot; epistolary series. A pastoral letter addressing a Christian woman who has fallen in love with an unbeliever and is asking whether her feelings confirm God&#39;s will for the relationship.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Points</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The faulty assumption:</strong> &quot;If God didn&#39;t want me with this person, He wouldn&#39;t have let me fall in love with him.&quot;</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Two problems with this reasoning:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>Feelings don&#39;t determine God&#39;s will.</em> Cain felt strongly about killing Abel; David burned for Bathsheba. Strong emotions are not divine approval. We can rebel against God with our passions just as we can obey Him.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>You chose your way into this.</em> You weren&#39;t pushed into the zone of vulnerability. You made repeated choices — casual conversations, deepening trust, emotional openness — that created the bond. God actually warned you against it through His Word and through the counsel of godly people around you. You ignored the rescue boats.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The &quot;zone of vulnerability&quot;</strong> (term from Douglas Wilson): the space where a man and woman become emotionally vulnerable with each other, creating a bond that <em>feels</em> God-ordained. It builds gradually: casual friendship → trust → appreciation → deep emotional sharing → romantic attachment.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The rescue boat analogy:</strong> The man on the roof who prays for rescue but rejects the boat and helicopter because he&#39;s waiting for God to act supernaturally. God answers through ordinary means — including His Word and the counsel of godly friends warning you now.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"concepts-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Concepts touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=courtship</a> — the danger of emotion-led pursuit outside God&#39;s design</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=biblical-manhood</a> — the corresponding male side of courtship</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=storytelling</a> — how narrative and feeling shape attachment</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"related-resources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related resources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=a-field-guide-to-being-a-faithful-man</a> — the male side: commitment over feelings</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=where-have-the-men-gone</a> — the male side of godly courtship</li>\n</ul>\n",
