      "created": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "faith",
      "excerpt": "Author: titus-jr-laxa\nPublished: 2024-12-25\nSource: tituslaxajr.substack.com A Christmas sermon/essay on Matthew 1:21. The world is troubled by sin — sin around us, sin in us, sin against us. The good news of Christmas...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"good-tidings-of-comfort-and-joy\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Good Tidings of Comfort and Joy</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2024-12-25\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> tituslaxajr.substack.com</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">A Christmas sermon/essay on Matthew 1:21. The world is troubled by sin — sin around us, sin in us, sin against us. The good news of Christmas is that Jesus came to save us from sin itself, not merely from hell.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Points</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Three kinds of trouble:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Sin around us</em> — toxic workplaces, Pride marches, fallen church leaders, difficult spouses and children</li>\n<li><em>Sin in us</em> — porn addiction that won&#39;t stop, bitterness, same-sex attraction, persistent besetting sins</li>\n<li><em>Sin against us</em> — betrayal, abandonment, wayward children, prodigal spouses</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Three things Jesus saves us from:</strong></p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">1. Blindness to sin.</strong> Pride makes it easy to see others&#39; sins but blind us to our own. Jesus comes as light, exposing sin not to shame but to cleanse. The response is confession — not of others&#39; sins, but our own.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">2. The burden of sin.</strong> Jesus became truly human to bear human burdens experientially (Heb. 4:15) and die as a substitute. His becoming flesh is also a <em>promise fulfilled</em> — proving He will accomplish all His other promises of sanctification. He who began a good work will complete it (Phil. 1:6).</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">3. The bastion of sin.</strong> Jesus came not just to save individuals but families, communities, nations. &quot;Immanuel — God with us&quot; is a battle name (cf. Joshua 1:9). The walls of sin around your loved ones&#39; hearts can come down like Jericho.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"concepts-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Concepts touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=incarnation</a> — Jesus as truly God and truly man; Christmas as the start of the decisive entry into history</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sanctification</a> — salvation from sin&#39;s power, not just sin&#39;s penalty</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a> — substitutionary death as the basis of all promises</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"related-resources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related resources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=the-incarnating-presence-of-jesus</a> — Titus&#39;s earlier Christmas essay on incarnation&#39;s weight</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=when-death-died</a> — the companion Good Friday meditation</li>\n</ul>\n",
