      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "work",
      "excerpt": "Author: titus-jr-laxa\nSource: raw/notes/Life In-Between.md (sermon notes) Sermon notes on Genesis 1:27-28. Addressed to young professionals navigating three kinds of pressure: situational (work stress), social (life...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"life-in-between\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Life In-Between</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> raw/notes/Life In-Between.md (sermon notes)</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Sermon notes on Genesis 1:27-28. Addressed to young professionals navigating three kinds of pressure: situational (work stress), social (life milestones), and sexual. The answer is found in God&#39;s original design for image-bearers.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Points</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Three pressures unique to this generation:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><em>Situational</em> — work, work, work; perpetual stress and the need to unwind</li>\n<li><em>Social</em> — milestone pressure: &quot;When are you getting a boyfriend? a spouse? children?&quot; from family, church, community</li>\n<li><em>Sexual</em> — men turning to pornography; women turning to social media for dopamine and validation</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Root cause:</strong> All three reduce to seeking <em>validation and satisfaction</em> — proving something about yourself.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">God&#39;s design (Genesis 1:27-28):</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Work</em>: The fallen mindset treats work as curse and burden. God&#39;s design is seed-to-growth — faithful, consistent plodding that blesses you and others.</li>\n<li><em>Relationship</em>: Man is not meant to be alone; he needs a <em>helper</em> — someone to help accomplish what God designed. The question &quot;help to what?&quot; matters: there are things only a spouse can help you do.</li>\n<li><em>Sexuality</em>: The male sex drive and female desire for intimacy are not bugs but design features — oriented toward fruitfulness and multiplication. Pornography and social media are cheap substitutes for the harder, more fulfilling work of marriage and family.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The solution:</strong> Exchange counterfeits for the real. Ask God for what He actually designed — and then put in the hard work of pursuing it through prayer, honesty, and perseverance.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"concepts-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Concepts touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=biblical-manhood</a> — God&#39;s design for male sexual identity and work</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=courtship</a> — pursuing marriage as hard and worthy work</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=worship</a> — work and fruitfulness as image-bearing vocation</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"areas-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Areas touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=work</a> — the fallen mindset vs. God&#39;s design for work</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=wiki/areas/parenting</a> — fruitfulness and multiplication as the telos of marriage</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"related-resources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related resources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=a-field-guide-to-being-a-faithful-man</a> — committed pursuit as the male calling</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=where-have-the-men-gone</a> — the practical challenge of godly courtship</li>\n</ul>\n",
