      "slug": "normalization-of-female-sexual-degeneracy",
      "title": "The Normalization of Female Sexual Degeneracy",
      "type": "resource",
      "tags": [
        "sexuality",
        "culture",
        "shame",
        "women",
        "media",
        "christianity"
      ],
      "created": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "culture",
      "excerpt": "Author: michael-foster | Source: thisisfoster.com | Published: 2026-04-03 Subtitle: The Porn Nobody Calls Porn --- The explosion of explicit romance and erotic fiction — driven largely by BookTok and self-publishing —...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"the-normalization-of-female-sexual-degeneracy\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Normalization of Female Sexual Degeneracy</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=michael-foster</a> | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> thisisfoster.com | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2026-04-03</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Subtitle: <em>The Porn Nobody Calls Porn</em></p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"core-argument\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Core argument</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The explosion of explicit romance and erotic fiction — driven largely by BookTok and self-publishing — is a parallel to male pornography, engineered to exploit the specific architecture of female arousal. It is being culturally normalized and even celebrated, while the mechanisms for shame that would otherwise protect women are being dismantled.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"female-arousal-architecture\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Female arousal architecture</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Research consistently shows women require <em>mental mapping</em> before arousal — an emotional narrative with relational stakes and tension. Men respond to visual stimulus with minimal context. This is why:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Online pornography skews heavily male</li>\n<li>Erotic content for women lives primarily in text — fan fiction, romance novels, audio erotica</li>\n<li>Women engage the same impulses men do, through a different medium</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Story is the optimal delivery mechanism for female arousal. The genre knows this and engineers accordingly.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"the-booktok-phenomenon\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The BookTok phenomenon</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Romance/erotica now accounts for ~20% of all book sales. Self-published titles are ~70% of romance e-book sales. The content is increasingly explicit and engineered for addictive escalation.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Author Sarah J. Maas is named as a case study: she deliberately times explicit scenes to coincide with emotional climaxes in the narrative, so that erotic release and narrative release fire simultaneously — creating inextricable linkage.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Genre taxonomy mirrors the difference in arousal: male pornography is categorized by sex act; female erotic fiction is categorized by relational dynamic (enemies to lovers, forced proximity, dark romance, morally gray interests).</p>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;Barnes and Noble... have now just become another kind of adult entertainment store.&quot; — Hilary Layne</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"the-removal-of-shame\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The removal of shame</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=shame</a> is described (via Layne) as a God-given signal: &quot;how our brains tell us we&#39;re doing something that will harm us.&quot;</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The cultural project around erotic fiction has systematically removed shame for women specifically, because historically women led the charge against indecent material. Two moves are identified:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Secular:</strong> sexual promiscuity recast as liberation, independence, a birthright. Guilt is absent from the narratives.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Christian:</strong> grace is real, but the fictional retelling presents redemption with no real cost. Sin is forgiven but the character still gets everything she wanted.</li>\n</ol>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>Redeeming Love</em> is cited as an early example in Christian circles — extended marital sex scenes, a kidnapping framed as romance, handed to women and daughters for 30 years.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"the-asymmetry\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The asymmetry</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Men who consume pornography compulsively carry shame (appropriate).</li>\n<li>Women who consume erotic fiction compulsively are told they are empowering themselves (profound harm).</li>\n<li>Research infrastructure reflects this: decades of studies on pornography&#39;s harm to men; almost none on erotic fiction&#39;s harm to women.</li>\n<li>The feminist framing has made critical inquiry nearly impossible.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-quotes\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key quotes</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;What shapes imagination will, sooner or later, shape desire, and desire does not stay contained.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;Porn is twisting our men... what is being called women&#39;s literature is twisting our women.&quot;</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"pages-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Pages touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=michael-foster</a> — author</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=shame</a> — key concept: shame as protective signal</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=culture</a> — area: broader cultural critique</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=faith</a> — area: Christian dimension of the problem</li>\n</ul>\n",
