      "slug": "some-thoughts-on-parenting-part-2",
      "title": "Some Thoughts on Parenting, Part 2: The Importance of Storytelling",
      "type": "resource",
      "tags": [
        "parenting",
        "storytelling",
        "family",
        "christianity",
        "formation"
      ],
      "created": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "culture",
      "excerpt": "Author: michael-foster | Source: thisisfoster.com | Published: 2026-03-21 --- Godly parenting requires becoming a storyteller. Stories are the primary medium through which children are formed — their identity, their...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"some-thoughts-on-parenting-part-2-the-importance-of-storytelling\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Some Thoughts on Parenting, Part 2: The Importance of Storytelling</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=michael-foster</a> | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> thisisfoster.com | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2026-03-21</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"core-argument\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Core argument</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Godly parenting requires becoming a storyteller. Stories are the primary medium through which children are formed — their identity, their understanding of the world, their moral intuitions. Three categories of stories are essential: Scripture, family history, and good fiction.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"biblical-narrative-as-the-master-story\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Biblical narrative as the master story</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Children must know the whole arc: <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">creation → fall → redemption → consummation</strong>. This means:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Teaching both individual stories (Adam, Abraham, Samuel, Paul) <em>and</em> the tapestry they form</li>\n<li>Using children&#39;s Bibles selectively for early years</li>\n<li>Leaning into the epic parts — Exodus, the judges, the kings, the battles — as entry points</li>\n<li>The goal: children begin to interpret the world through Scripture, comparing real people to biblical ones</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"family-stories-as-a-family-genesis\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Family stories as a family Genesis</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The word <em>Genesis</em> means origin, source, beginning. Family stories function the same way on a smaller scale — they tell children:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Where they came from</li>\n<li>Why certain traditions stuck</li>\n<li>Why some relationships are strained</li>\n<li>Why Grandpa drank too much; why an uncle disappeared</li>\n<li>How God&#39;s mercy appeared in ordinary life</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;They display the reality of sin, consequence, mercy, and providence.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">These stories are not sentimental — they are identity-forming. Children who don&#39;t receive them lose access to lived examples of the gospel at human scale.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Foster&#39;s great-grandmother, 99 years old with some dementia, still told a story about buying cookies for a penny. That story passed through generations. That&#39;s the scale of what&#39;s at stake.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"reading-and-fiction\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Reading and fiction</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Start early and simple to build the habit and the love of it</li>\n<li>Avoid overly moralized stories — they backfire; better to <em>show</em> what&#39;s good than to hammer a lesson</li>\n<li>Recommended: <em>Little Bear</em>, <em>Frog and Toad</em>, <em>Wizard of Oz</em>, <em>Chronicles of Narnia</em>, <em>My Side of the Mountain</em>, missionary biographies (especially Hudson Taylor)</li>\n<li>Audiobooks are acceptable — the main thing is getting good stories in</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;A good story tells the truth, one way or another. Sometimes fiction does that best... In that sense, some of the truest stories ever told are the ones that never happened.&quot;</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"storytelling-as-active-practice\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Storytelling as active practice</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Foster describes a family game: give kids a setting, a character type, and a plot, then improvise a story on the spot. The stories were often ridiculous. The kids loved it and still remember it. The point: storytelling doesn&#39;t need to be polished — it needs to happen.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Story time is both planned (family devotions, bedtime reading) and unplanned (campfires, dinner tables, funeral meals).</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"connection-to-entry-html-slug-storytelling-concept\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Connection to <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=storytelling</a> concept</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The article is the most direct treatment of storytelling as a formational practice in the wiki so far. The idea that story is the shape of reality — that God Himself tells the world&#39;s story through Scripture — recurs in related sources.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"pages-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Pages touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=michael-foster</a> — author</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=storytelling</a> — core concept explored here</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=wiki/areas/parenting</a> — area: family and child-rearing</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=faith</a> — area: Scripture, biblical narrative</li>\n</ul>\n",
