      "updated": "Sat Apr 11 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "faith",
      "excerpt": "Author: titus-jr-laxa | Source: tituslaxajr.substack.com | Published: 2025-12-25 Written by Titus Jr himself — a Christmas reflection on John 1:9-14. --- \"And the Word became flesh and dwelt among us, and we have seen...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"the-incarnating-presence-of-jesus\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Incarnating Presence of Jesus</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> tituslaxajr.substack.com | <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> 2025-12-25</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>Written by Titus Jr himself — a Christmas reflection on John 1:9-14.</em></p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"core-text\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Core text</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;And the Word became flesh and dwelt among us, and we have seen his glory, glory as of the only Son from the Father, full of grace and truth.&quot; — John 1:14</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"core-argument\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Core argument</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=incarnation</a> is often treated as a doctrinal formality — memorized for apologetics, rehearsed at Christmas, then set aside. But understanding what it means that God became flesh changes how we see God&#39;s presence entirely. The incarnation reveals that God&#39;s presence is:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Real</strong> — not abstract, ethereal, or imaginary. As real as light in darkness, as a newborn to new parents, as a bride walking the aisle.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Intrusive</strong> — He entered a world that did not know Him, among a people who did not receive Him. His presence exposes darkness by nature. It is not enough to point to blessings as evidence of God&#39;s presence — His presence should mean sin is constantly exposed and confronted, not hidden and tolerated.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Changing</strong> — To all who receive Him, He gives the right to become children of God. Not by willpower or wishful thinking, but by God&#39;s power. His presence cannot leave you unchanged — <em>&quot;like a ten-wheeler truck rushing through the highway. If you are hit, you cannot be unchanged.&quot;</em></li>\n</ol>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"theological-connections\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Theological connections</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Connects to <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a>: the incarnation is the precondition for the cross. Christ had to become flesh in order to die.</li>\n<li>Connects to <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=resurrection</a>: the same body that became flesh was raised bodily. The incarnation guarantees the resurrection is a human resurrection.</li>\n<li>The article frames Christmas as carrying the same weight as Good Friday — both are moments of God decisively entering history.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-quote\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key quote</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;His presence truly changes sinners into saints, rebels into followers, slaves to sin into freedmen, and men of apathy into ambassadors.&quot;</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"pages-touched\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Pages touched</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> — author (Titus Jr&#39;s own writing)</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=incarnation</a> — core concept developed here</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=faith</a> — area: Christology, Christmas</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a> — connected concept: incarnation enables the cross</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=resurrection</a> — connected concept: incarnation guarantees a bodily resurrection</li>\n</ul>\n",
