      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "faith",
      "excerpt": "Author: douglas-wilson\nPublished: April 4, 2026 (Good Friday)\nSource: [dougwils.com](https://dougwils.com/the-church/when-death-died.html) --- A Good Friday meditation arguing that death's defeat was accomplished on the...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"when-death-died\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">When Death Died</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Author:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=douglas-wilson</a>\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Published:</strong> April 4, 2026 (Good Friday)\n<strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Source:</strong> <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">https://dougwils.com/the-church/when-death-died.html</a></p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"summary\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Summary</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">A Good Friday meditation arguing that death&#39;s defeat was accomplished on the cross — not at the resurrection. The resurrection is the <em>proof</em> and <em>triumphal parade</em> of a victory already won. When Jesus said &quot;It is finished,&quot; that was the death blow to death itself.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-points\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key points</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The cross is the agonistic victory.</strong> The resurrection is the aftermath — the triumphal procession. The battle was won when Jesus died.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Death died when Jesus died.</strong> Jesus destroyed &quot;him that had the power of death&quot; (Heb. 2:14) <em>through</em> His death. The principalities and powers were nailed to the cross (Col. 2:14–15).</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Jesus descended into the grave with His arms full.</strong> In dying, He embraced the law against us, our sins, and the devil together with his accusations — and escorted them all down to the depths so they could remain dead forever.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The resurrection proves death is dead.</strong> It does not accomplish the death of death — it confirms it.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Good Friday is not a funeral.</strong> It is a victory celebration. We stand on the battlefield where death itself lies prostrate.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The Eucharist is a weekly Easter.</strong> The broken body and shed blood are emblems of victory, not grief. Every Lord&#39;s Day is a celebration of the cross.</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">The chain: sin → death.</strong> Death died when sin died; sin died when Jesus died. The law, sin, death, and the devil — all slain together.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-quotes\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key quotes</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;When the Lord cried out, &#39;It is finished,&#39; it was that moment when death received its death blow.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;In His death, He took them all <em>away</em>.&quot;</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;The resurrection is not the death of death — that happened on the cross.&quot;</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"scripture-referenced\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Scripture referenced</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Hebrews 2:14 — Christ destroyed the devil through death</li>\n<li>Colossians 2:14–15 — principalities nailed to the cross</li>\n<li>John 12:31–32 — &quot;now shall the prince of this world be cast out&quot;</li>\n<li>Psalm 103:12 — transgressions removed as far as east from west</li>\n<li>Micah 7:19 — sins cast into the depths of the sea</li>\n<li>1 Corinthians 15:56–57 — the sting of death is sin; victory through Christ</li>\n<li>1 Corinthians 11:26 — proclaiming the Lord&#39;s death in Communion</li>\n<li>Romans 6:23 — the wages of sin is death</li>\n</ul>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"connected-pages\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Connected pages</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=douglas-wilson</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=atonement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=resurrection</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=faith</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
