      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "ministry",
      "excerpt": "Ephesians 4 presents two kinds of unity: one we already have and must preserve, and one we do not yet possess and must grow toward. Confusing these two produces either complacency (treating future unity as already...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"church-unity\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Church Unity</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Ephesians 4 presents two kinds of unity: one we already have and must preserve, and one we do not yet possess and must grow toward. Confusing these two produces either complacency (treating future unity as already achieved) or despair (treating present unity as failure).</p>\n<h1 id=\"the-unity-of-the-spirit-eph-4-2-3\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Unity of the Spirit (Eph. 4:2–3)</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;With all lowliness and meekness, with longsuffering, forbearing one another in love; Endeavouring to keep the unity of the Spirit in the bond of peace.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">This is a <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">given unity</strong>. We have it by grace. When you have fellowship with a believer on an airplane, this is that kind of unity.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">We do not attain this unity—we <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">preserve</strong> it. We keep what we already have by not sinning against one another. This requires lowliness, meekness, patience, forbearance in love.</p>\n<h1 id=\"the-unity-of-the-faith-eph-4-11-13\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Unity of the Faith (Eph. 4:11–13)</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;Till we all come in the unity of the faith, and of the knowledge of the Son of God, unto a perfect man, unto the measure of the stature of the fulness of Christ.&quot;</blockquote>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">This is a <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">future unity</strong>. We grow toward it through the exercise of apostles, prophets, evangelists, pastors, teachers. The gifts build up the body over time, over centuries.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">We are not there yet. We are not supposed to be there yet. The building is only partially complete.</p>\n<h1 id=\"rome-39-s-error\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Rome&#39;s Error</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Rome&#39;s view of unity puts on the trusses early—claiming the unity of the faith before its time. But the church will be without spot or blemish (Eph. 5:27) at the Eschaton. Patience.</p>\n<h1 id=\"the-voluntarist-system\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Voluntarist System</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Until the unity of the faith arrives, established state churches don&#39;t work any better than other monopolies. They get fat and lazy. Competition—within Eph. 4:2-3 limits—is healthy.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">The gas stations have gas. That&#39;s why most of those twenty churches hold to and preach the gospel—because people can drive by to find &quot;their&quot; church.</p>\n<h1 id=\"related-concepts\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Related Concepts</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=sola-scriptura</a> — Scripture alone as ultimate authority</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=providence</a> — Christ&#39;s hand building His church</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=faith</a> — Christian faith, theology, formation</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"sources\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Sources</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=untidy-protestantism</a> — Douglas Wilson on the two unities of Ephesians 4</li>\n</ul>\n",
