      "slug": "the-sloth-vs-the-diligent",
      "title": "The Sloth vs. the Diligent",
      "type": "resource",
      "tags": [
        "discipline",
        "wisdom",
        "work",
        "education",
        "faithfulness"
      ],
      "created": "Fri Apr 17 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "updated": "Fri Apr 17 2026 08:00:00 GMT+0800 (Philippine Standard Time)",
      "sources": 1,
      "domain": "work",
      "excerpt": "Titus Jr Laxa · [Substack](https://tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/the-sloth-vs-the-diligent) · Published 2024-05-16\nAlso posted at kapatidministry.org ![white cat sleeps under white...",
      "htmlContent": "<h1 id=\"the-sloth-vs-the-diligent\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Sloth vs. the Diligent</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>Titus Jr Laxa · <a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">https://tituslaxajr.substack.com/p/the-sloth-vs-the-diligent</a> · Published 2024-05-16</em>\n<em>Also posted at kapatidministry.org</em></p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><figure class=\"my-12\"><img src=\"\" alt=\"\" class=\"w-full object-cover\" /></figure>\n</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><em>Photo by Kate Stone Matheson on Unsplash</em></p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"the-text\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Text</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\"><em>Whoever is slothful will not roast his game, but the diligent man will get precious wealth.</em>\n— Proverbs 12:27</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"core-argument\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Core Argument</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Laziness among young people is not a matter of doing less — many students are busy. The problem is expressed through procrastination and the misuse of time: hours on TikTok or Instagram Reels, followed by crisis-mode work under deadline. Titus Jr names two patterns young people use to fake diligence:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Intensity</strong> — Compressing 48 hours of work into 24 hours (Doug Wilson&#39;s term)</li>\n<li><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">Extension</strong> — Working overtime on tasks that required overtime only because of procrastination</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Both are symptoms of slothfulness wearing the mask of effort.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"two-truths-from-proverbs-12-27\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Two Truths from Proverbs 12:27</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">1. Slothfulness produces half-cooked work.</strong> The cramming student produces an incoherent paper. The athlete who trains one day before the game risks injury and poor performance. The &quot;Saturday Night Special&quot; sermon is less confident, more repetitive. God&#39;s word: the slothful will not roast his game — will not fulfil the potential he had if he had been diligent.</p>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\"><strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">2. Diligence produces precious wealth — but only if diligence is rightly defined.</strong> Diligence is not intensity; it is <strong class=\"text-on-surface font-semibold\">faithful, consistent work over time</strong>. Fifteen minutes per day on a research paper, sustained, produces better work without the crunch — and builds the habits of knowledge, wisdom, time management, self-control, and ultimately spiritual trust in a God whose returns are slow but sure.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"the-spiritual-dimension\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">The Spiritual Dimension</h1>\n<p class=\"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-on-surface-variant\">Diligence over time requires trusting God when results are not immediately visible. This is the hidden wealth: the discipline itself becomes faith — dependence on God even when the outcome is not yet apparent.</p>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"key-quote\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Key Quote</h1>\n<blockquote class=\"pl-8 border-l-2 border-primary-container italic text-xl font-headline text-on-primary-container py-2 my-12\">&quot;Let us start to shed our slothful skins, and start being diligent in the responsibilities being given to us... Let us turn to God and plead with Him to give us a heart and hands to not do things half-cooked by postponing them to the last-minute, but to start on them early, consistently, and faithfully.&quot;</blockquote>\n<hr class=\"my-12 border-0 border-t border-outline-variant/20\">\n<h1 id=\"pages-updated\" class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-headline text-on-surface mt-16 mb-6\">Pages Updated</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=discipline</a> — faithfulness over time as the shape of diligence</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=wisdom</a> — diligence as the path to practical wisdom</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=work</a> — theology of ordinary work and effort</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=education</a> — directly addressed to students and teachers</li>\n<li><a href=\"#\" class=\"text-primary underline decoration-primary/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-primary transition-all\">entry.html?slug=titus-jr-laxa</a> — resource added</li>\n</ul>\n",
